Title: Agreement with U.S. 'within reach' if it ensures enrichment and lifts sanctions: Araqchi.

Relevant extracted text:
- Foreign Minister Abbas Araqchi said an agreement with the United States was within reach if Iran's right to uranium enrichment was guaranteed and sanctions against Tehran were lifted.
- The remarks were made ahead of the upcoming sixth round of indirect talks between Tehran and Washington on Iran's nuclear program, scheduled for June 15 in Muscat, Oman.
- The talks were mediated by Oman and had faced hurdles because the U.S. administration was pushing for a complete halt to Iran's uranium enrichment, a demand Tehran had rejected.
- Araqchi said Iran had no intention of developing nuclear weapons and that this premise could form the main foundation for a deal.
- He said that as talks resumed Sunday, an agreement ensuring the peaceful nature of Iran's nuclear program was within reach and could be achieved quickly.
- IRNA reported that a mutually beneficial outcome would hinge on recognition of Iran's right to enrichment under UN watchdog supervision and effective termination of sanctions.

This capture describes conditional negotiations and a possible nuclear-program agreement; it does not report that Iran and the United States had already established a permanent peace deal ending military hostilities.